# Fix Alarm and Notification System

The alarm system does not fire notifications or ring because the app never requests the runtime `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission (introduced in Android 13 / API 33). Consequently, all notifications are silently blocked by the operating system. In addition, the notification channels do not play an explicit alarm sound or vibrate, which is necessary for the app to "ring".

This plan addresses:
1. Requesting the `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` runtime permission on app startup.
2. Configuring high-priority notification channels (Medicine, Meeting, Deadline) with the default system alarm ringtone, audio attributes, and vibration pattern.
3. Updating channel IDs to force the system to recreate the channels with the new sound/vibrations.
4. Improving database query robustness for rescheduling snoozed alarms after boot.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since notification permissions are required on Android 13+ (API 33+), the user will be prompted for notification permissions upon launching the application.
> Channel IDs will be migrated to `*_v2` (e.g. `channel_medicine_v2`) to force the OS to recreate them. Old channels will remain registered but unused, which is standard Android behavior when updating notification channels.

